<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/746066-i-am-trying-to-figure-out-where-charles">I am trying to figure out where Charles Lenox lives. How can he live in Mayfair and drink his coffee by a window looking out on St. James Park?

If he does live in Mayfair (north of Green Park) and is looking toward Westminster, wouldn&#39;t Buckingham Palace be on his right and St. James Palace be on his left (instead of the opposite as stated in the first chapter?)

Why am I spending my time on this? LOL!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_746066'><a id="like_count_community_question_746066" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/746066?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">11 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1044816.A_Beautiful_Blue_Death">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/746066-i-am-trying-to-figure-out-where-charles">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/746066-i-am-trying-to-figure-out-where-charles">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1698850-luvs2read"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1698850-luvs2read">Luvs2read</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It is likely &quot;Hampden Lane&quot; is a fictional street. It would have to be somewhere between the Mall and Pall Mall (maybe Carlton House Terrace), but tha<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It is likely "Hampden Lane" is a fictional street. It would have to be somewhere between the Mall and Pall Mall (maybe Carlton House Terrace), but that would put it in St. James's. If on the other side of the park, it would be in Westminster. I did find small historical inaccuracies in the book, alongside very good historical details.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
