              <span id="reviewTextContainer2150675866" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15842608778456807280">1st read - Paperback, 309 pages<br/>4 Stars<br/><br/>I really enjoyed this book; historical fiction with a mystery is one of the best genres for me right now [I absolutely adore the Maisie Dobbs series, which is HF/M genre and they are also delightful] and this fits the bill fantastically. Great characters, a very likable MC and a very good mystery. I thought I had the murderer figured out; I was wrong. Kind of. They were still a very bad person, but not prone to murder. Which always makes the book better - I </span>
  <span id="freeText15842608778456807280" style="display:none">1st read - Paperback, 309 pages<br />4 Stars<br /><br />I really enjoyed this book; historical fiction with a mystery is one of the best genres for me right now [I absolutely adore the Maisie Dobbs series, which is HF/M genre and they are also delightful] and this fits the bill fantastically. Great characters, a very likable MC and a very good mystery. I thought I had the murderer figured out; I was wrong. Kind of. They were still a very bad person, but not prone to murder. Which always makes the book better - I love it when I do not figure it out. <br />This was a great start to a series and I am so glad that I took a risk on a book that just looked cool and I thought I might like! ;-)<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Second read - Kindle, 340 pages<br />Book club pick October - Mom's pick<br />5 Stars [bumped up from 4]<br /><br />THIS was even better the second time around. WOW I just love this series!!! <br />For a book that I bought simply for the cover, it has brought much joy to me and my mom and most of the people I have shoved the book at!! ;-)</span>
  <a data-text-id="15842608778456807280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

